    "\n",
    "### Question 1d\n",
    "\n",
    "What were the central problems with the earlier property tax system in Cook County as reported by the Chicago Tribune? What were the primary causes of these problems? \n",
    "\n",
    "**Note:** Along with reading the paragraph above, you will need to watch [Lecture 15](https://ds100.org/fa24/lecture/lec15/) to answer this question."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The central problem with the earlier property tax system in Cook County is that the lower-income population was being charged proportionally more property tax than the higher income population. The primary cause of this was that the assessment/model used to generate how much property tax a property owed produced innaccurate assessments of the values of properties in Cook county, systematically overvalueing lower-priced properties and undervalueing higher-priced properties, which resulted in an inaccurate taxation system that taxed poorer (often non-white) residents of Cook county proportionally more than richer (often white) residents."
   ]
  },
